What growth is projected in your country?
Follow @ecfin for more on the spring economic forecast and check out the interactive map → https://t.co/JNIRDIrk2r #ECForecast https://t.co/M9cC4GszZp

Public finances are improving, with no deficits over 3% of GDP.
The aggregate general government deficit of the euro area is now forecast to fall to 0.7% of GDP in 2018 and 0.6% in 2019. #ECForecast https://t.co/WYa6InU5Ta

Europe continues to enjoy robust growth, which has helped drive unemployment to a 10-year low.
Unemployment is now around pre-crisis levels and is set to continue to decline. #ECForecast https://t.co/OPkzaBXdcd

Growth rates for the EU and the euro area beat expectations in 2017 to reach a 10-year high at 2.4%.
Growth set to remain strong in 2018 and ease only slightly in 2019, with growth of 2.3% in EU and 2.0% in euro area. 
https://t.co/nqBZUpQMrk #ECForecast https://t.co/t34TUzuqtn

The EU is founded on the values of democracy, human rights and the rule of law, on free and pluralistic media as enshrined in the EU's  fundamental rights charter. #WorldPressFreedomDay https://t.co/CyQswt1QQ6

data.text:
"The new budget is an opportunity to shape our future as a new, ambitious Union of 27 bound together by solidarity. With today's proposal we have put forward a pragmatic plan for how to do more with less."
@JunckerEU @GOettingerEU #EUbudget #FutureofEurope https://t.co/AHf2ZPRlcZ

We are making ambitious yet realistic proposals for a modern #EUBudget. 
Learn more about today's proposals
→ In our press release https://t.co/KAuP6gmSnf
→ In our Q&A https://t.co/VdE7ZoUCXF
→ In our factsheets https://t.co/CU4STxwM0K
→ On our website https://t.co/HoIyJEGXWn https://t.co/a0wy5b95D2

We want to increase the effectiveness of EU's external policies, strengthen coordination and give the EU the flexibility for a faster response to new crises and challenges.

Our #EUBudget proposal on #EUinTheWorld explained ↓ https://t.co/VteCcBWMfG

We want to reinforce funding for external action by 26% to reach €120 billion, with a specific emphasis on Europe's neighbourhood and preserving a reserve to deal with emerging challenges #EUIntheWorld https://t.co/nqCeG6Up7j

The EU needs to take greater responsibility for defending and protecting its citizens. 
We propose tools to help them in this effort: the European Defence fund, #PESCO, the European Peace Facility, #HorizonEU...

Our #EUBudget proposal on #EUdefence explained ↓ https://t.co/hgbvkokFaM

Security threats know no borders. 
No Member State can, or should meet them on its own. 
The EU Budget should support them in their efforts to keep Europeans safe.

Our #EUBudget proposal on #SecurityUnion explained ↓ https://t.co/ej4zjLQYiq

It is the most basic of rights to feel safe and secure.
We propose to increase investment in security by 40% to reach €4.8 billion and to create a €13 billion #EUDefence Fund to complement and catalyse national expenditure in research and capability development. #SecurityUnion https://t.co/5Amc4RqnzL

More efficient search and rescue capacities to save lives
An effective and humane return policy
An effective protection of our external borders

Our #EUBudget proposal on #MigrationEU explained ↓ https://t.co/E0YNSQCvv2

We want to triple expenditure for the management of external borders, migration and asylum. 
We are also proposing to create a new Integrated Border Management Fund to help guarantee a high level of security in the EU #EUBorderGuard #MigrationEU https://t.co/PHixMxy8F5

A modernised Common Agricultural Policy to ensure access to high quality food and a fully integrated #SingleMarket. Climate and environment, sustainable agrisector and development of rural areas.
   
Our #EUBudget proposal on #FutureofCAP explained ↓ https://t.co/kligDqzzCx

data.text:
We propose to raise the level of ambition for #ClimateAction, with a target of at least 25% of EU expenditure contributing to climate objectives.
   
Our #EUBudget proposal on sustainability, environment protection and fight against climate change explained ↓ https://t.co/KcKkDnvFQ6

The EU is a global frontrunner in #ClimateAction
We are proposing to modernise the Common Agricultural Policy to put a greater emphasis on environment #FutureOfCAP https://t.co/dnYnk9T6Yx

We propose two new instruments to modernise the economy and enhance stability: a Reform Support Programme and a European Investment Stabilisation Function  

Our #EUBudget proposal on #DeepeningEMU explained ↓ https://t.co/7T3cCxyiEJ

We invest in people, the heart of the European project. 
Always.
We want to double the size of #ErasmusPlus and #EUSolidarityCorps. 
We propose  a new Creative Europe and a new Justice, Rights and Value programme. 

Our #EUBudget proposal on investing in people explained ↓ https://t.co/5DPr6tTH8m

Research and innovation, small businesses, better health and education, skills, jobs and social inclusion. Fairer opportunities for all.

Our #EUBudget proposal on regional development and #CohesionPolicy explained ↓ https://t.co/CAxhNyD6iB

We propose a simplified framework for our #CohesionPolicy and less red tape for the beneficiaries. We also want to strengthen its link with the #EuropeanSemester to support growth-friendly reforms. https://t.co/73XbnYdIKP

From #ArtificialIntelligence to #DigitalSkills. From personalised medicine based on supercomputer calculations to EU's response cyberattacks and crimes. 
   
Our #EUBudget proposal on digital transformation explained ↓ https://t.co/5YE2jYL59f

Europe's future investment depends on decisions we take today.
Renewable energies, research, innovation, entrepreneurship, #digitisation, #skills #CircularEconomy….
   
Our #EUBudget proposal on investments explained ↓ https://t.co/YE4FZExBy8

EU funds for research and innovation are vital.
New planets discovered, major advances made in cancer treatment, millions of Ebola vaccine doses available… 

Our #EUBudget proposal on research and innovation explained ↓ https://t.co/sMbjTlSetR

We want to increase investment in research and innovation by 50% for the flagship programmes #HorizonEU and increase by 9 investments in digital transformation and networks #investEU https://t.co/6tKqh1PWjV

New rules to shield #EUBudget from financial risks linked to generalised deficiencies as regards the rule of law. 
Only an independent judiciary that upholds the #RuleOfLaw and legal certainty in EU countries can guarantee that money is protected. https://t.co/E4T0x5en7b

A basket of new own resources, Common Consolidated Corporate Tax base, EU Emissions Trading System…
Our proposal on own resources explained: how it will work and how much money it will bring to the #EUBudget https://t.co/1AHkIKcKGi

We are proposing a #EUBudget of €1.135 billion in commitments over the period from 2021 to 2027, equivalent to 1.11% of the EU27's gross national income. Taking inflation into account, this would amount to €1.279 billion in commitments. https://t.co/L0XlIiSx9m

We are proposing a modern, simple and flexible #EUBudget for the 2021-2027 period. By focusing on the areas where the Union is best placed to deliver, we are building a Europe that protects, empowers and defends → https://t.co/HoIyJEGXWn #FutureOfEurope https://t.co/fTLM2EA1a3
